News24 Correspondent (File photo) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Polokwane - Economic Freedom Fighter leader Julius Malema on Sunday spent Christmas Day with hundreds of children at his hometown of Seshego, in Polokwane.&nbsp; &nbsp;Children from all over the township and surrounding areas gathered at Malema&rsquo;s township to celebrate one of the most important days on the Christian calendar with gifts and decent lunch.&ldquo;Many of them came from poverty stricken backgrounds, many of them have never experienced a good Christmas,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;We thought it was important that we celebrate with the poor of the poorest. Make it a Christmas to remember,&rdquo; said MalemaHe encouraged his guests to focus on their education, and cautioned them against the use of drugs.&ldquo;Take education seriously, and respect your parents and educators,&rdquo; was his message to children. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.